isted   ui-resizable\"><div class=\"asset-header ng-binding\"></div><div class=\"head editable ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-valid ng-binding ng-scope ng-not-empty None\" ng-paste=\"removeFormat($event, item.title)\"><h5>Lesson Summary<br></h5></div><div class=\"caption ng-binding\"></div></li><li id=\"mErwe\" data-space=\"\" full-editor=\"\" class=\"component list list-item, listed selected-class   ui-resizable border\"><div class=\"asset-header ng-binding\"></div><div ng-paste=\"removeFormat($event, item.title)\" class=\"list-item editable ng-pristine ng-valid ng-binding ng-scope ng-not-empty None ng-touched\" spellcheck=\"false\"><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"\">A corporation is a business entity of a special kind. It is the most significant kind of modern business organization</li><li class=\"\">Every country has its own legal requirement for the incorporation process</li><li class=\"\">The endpoint in the life of a corporation is through another formal process called liquidation<br></li><li class=\"\">Ethical conduct means to act according to the new global paradigms</li><li class=\"\">Sustainability and sustainable development are not identical concepts but they are linked<br></li><li class=\"\">A stakeholder is any person or a group, who is affected by or can affect the organizational objectives of a business</li><li class=\"\">Corporate culture, corporate norms and policies are known to have a significant influence on the choices, behaviours and decisions of corporate employees</li><li class=\"\">Business ethics is a specialized study of ethical right and wrong</li><li class=\"\">Unlike the laws, the rules of ethics are not created by a legislative</li><li class=\"\">The reasons why a corporation should be ethical could be situational, contextual reasons, strategic or pragmatic&nbsp;<br></li></ul></div><div class=\"caption ng-binding\"></div></li></ul>\n","\n<ul class=\"maintree ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-valid ng-isolate-scope ui-sortable ng-not-empty\"><li id=