ding\"></div><div class=\"head editable ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-valid ng-binding ng-scope ng-not-empty None\" ng-paste=\"removeFormat($event, item.title)\"><h5><b>Lesson Summary</b></h5></div><div class=\"caption ng-binding\"></div></li><li id=\"TvcQX\" data-space=\"\" full-editor=\"\" class=\"component list list-item, listed selected-class   border ui-resizable\"><div class=\"asset-header ng-binding\"></div><div ng-paste=\"removeFormat($event, item.title)\" class=\"list-item editable ng-pristine ng-valid ng-binding ng-scope ng-not-empty None ng-touched\" spellcheck=\"false\"><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"\">The theories of normative ethics are supposed to provide guidance. Moreover, they are also supposed to explain why a certain action is right or wrong<br></li><li class=\"\">There are two broad divisions of normative ethical theories which are consequentialist theories and non-consequentialist <span>theories</span></li><li class=\"\"><span>There is a big element in utilitarianism known as the cost-benefit analysis which looks into consequences in details and this is supposed to be&nbsp;</span>done before one engages in the action</li><li class=\"\">The Deon in deontological ethics stands for the Greek term Deon which means duty</li><li class=\"\">Kant reminds us that there can be duties that we impose on ourselves; internally imposed or self-imposed orders</li><li class=\"\">Rights can be defined as an entitlement to something</li><li class=\"\">There are two types of rights - legal rights and moral rights</li><li class=\"\">Typically in distributive justice, discourse is talked often in terms of society and social policies<br></li><li class=\"\">The pursuit of virtue is a continuous process</li><li class=\"\">Care ethics urges the moral agent to recognize the network of interpersonal and social relations that he/she is situated in</li></ul></div><div class=\"caption ng-binding\"></div></li></ul>\n"]}